  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">EU Project 2015-2018: Social Rights and Health (Natal, Sao Paulo and Bras&#xED;lia)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is a three-year project on social rights and public health in Brazil.

The Economic Justice Programme in Brazil has been focusing its work on universalization and defence of social protection, which encompasses health, social welfare and pensions, as a key public policy to tackle poverty and inequality. 

So far, health has been the area within social protection where the Programme has had limited opportunity to actively contribute and engage in. In the city of Natal, in northeast Brazil, the national health system has experienced three subsequent states of emergency in the last two years. This context has reinforced the need for development of grounded interventions on health both to address critical situations as well as to inform the Programme&#x2019;s advocacy.

This project seeks to contribute to the improvement of Brazil&#x2019;s SUS public health system and to increased access by poor and marginalised sectors of the population to public health services, reducing inequalities in access to social security.</narrative>
  </description>
